 To save where the character will look even before they actually rotate, you'll want to create a separate variable to store the intended look direction. Here's how to implement this:\n\n## Solution: Add Desired Look Direction Storage\n\n### 1. Add a new variable to your Player_BP:\n- **Variable Name**: `DesiredLookRotation`\n- **Type**: `Rotator`\n- **Default Value**: `(0, 0, 0)`\n\n### 2. Modify your look input handling:\n\nCurrently, your `IA_Look_0` input directly controls the character rotation with `AddControllerYawInput` and `AddControllerPitchInput`. To save the intended look direction:\n\n**Option A: Store the intended rotation separately**\n```\nIA_Look_0 (Triggered) \n→ Store current Control Rotation in DesiredLookRotation\n→ Add to DesiredLookRotation.Yaw (ActionValue_X)\n→ Add to DesiredLookRotation.Pitch (ActionValue_Y * -1)\n→ [Optional] Apply DesiredLookRotation to actual Control Rotation based on conditions\n```\n\n**Option B: Always update desired direction, conditionally apply to character**\n```\nIA_Look_0 (Triggered)\n→ Update DesiredLookRotation\n→ Branch: If should rotate character immediately\n   → Apply DesiredLookRotation to Control Rotation\n   → Else: Keep DesiredLookRotation stored for later use\n```\n\n### 3. Usage examples for the stored look direction:\n\n1. **Delayed Character Rotation**: Apply `DesiredLookRotation` to the character after a timer or when certain conditions are met\n\n2. **Aiming System**: Use `DesiredLookRotation` for weapon aiming while keeping character facing forward\n\n3. **Camera Control**: Have camera follow `DesiredLookRotation` while character rotates separately\n\n4. **Animation Blending**: Use the difference between actual rotation and `DesiredLookRotation` for look-at animations\n\n### 4. Implementation in your targeting system:\n\nYou can modify your targeting logic to also update `DesiredLookRotation`:\n\n```\nWhen Target Found → Set DesiredLookRotation to LookAt rotation toward target\nThis way the intended look direction is saved even before the character actually rotates\n```\n\nWould you like me to help you implement any specific part of this system? For example, I can show you how to:\n- Create the variable and modify the input handling\n- Add conditional rotation based on movement state\n- Integrate this with your existing targeting system\n- Use the stored direction for specific gameplay mechanics"},{"type":"checkpoint","info":{"id":"1f0ab4b8-c1ce-60ac-8005-254c823e7de8"}}]}],"Mapping":{"node_agent_names":{"pairs":[{"first":"ADEFBBDA4B47762A07A05FBA01000DAB","second":"ConstructionScript_0"},{"first":"DE2F432B40720C3C2E667780E5C90E47","second":"CastToPlayerController_0"},{"first":"DEC63E6F4FA5D1C6D77CDAA69A3665B7","second":"EventBeginPlay_0"},{"first":"8660AE93468D1B3F20B2108487CA3DED","second":"IsValid_0"},{"first":"FBF899404F21A0667C42FCA5D8BF45B3","second":"GetController_0"},{"first":"8257F383485E00F09814F8937491D337","second":"GetEnhancedInputLocalPlayerSubsystem_0"},{"first":"087E7C7F4376411E23405C9894A062F4","second":"AddRerouteNode..._0"},{"first":"D00F24C04D6578B7A08E61A0DD8A08AE","second":"AddMappingContext_0"},{"first":"350400164DC7FDAB561AAB83387D9334","second":"AddControllerYawInput_0"},{"first":"937F6788444FB33B39C6F185182A3A83","second":"float*float_0"},{"first":"A16D28944928D07E71F5AFA0FF78FA74","second":"IA_Look_0"},{"first":"4E1B2A974ABE23DDC460CAAB0FA06136","second":"AddControllerPitchInput_0"},{"first":"1ECD54264029A3EB4897A9A22DBFF41C","second":"AddComment..._0"},{"first":"78BDDC734363B6813DCB21BBB26255A4","second":"DetectMovementKeys_0"},{"first":"DB6A58FA4243687BD5A780B90F680C4C","second":"AddRerouteNode..._1"},{"first":"3C4BDC7D4FD01B20D271A3AA6CC574BB","second":"AddRerouteNode..._2"},{"first":"11FC62734D52BD10F5F9E39E91E5D9DE","second":"IA_Move_0"},{"first":"9D66E01E4CCC35188EA69B94B79F81C0","second":"AddMovementInput_0"},{"first":"6B1402E54C319CF133DAD9B1F59FD2C6","second":"GetRightVector_0"},{"first":"72A001864FBDD99AE609DFB462062A12"